\b7NAME\c9
\tio - standard Lua IO library

\b7DESCRIPTION\c9
\t\b7io\c9 is a reimplementation of the PUC-Rio Lua's \b7io\c9 API.

\b7FUNCTIONS\c9
\t\b2io.open\b4(\b7file\c9:\b3string\c9[, \b7mode\c9:\b3string\c9]\b4)\c9: \b5FILE*\c9 or \b5nil\c9, \b3string\c9
\tOpens the provided \b3file\c9 using the provided \b3mode\c9 (must be one of: `a', `r', `w').  Returns \b5nil\c9 and an error message on failure.

\t\b2io.input\b4(\c9[\b7file\c9:\b3string\c9 or \b5FILE*\c9]\b4)\c9: \b5FILE*\c9
\t\tReturns the current input stream, by default the standard input.  If \b5file\c9 is provided, changes the input stream.

\t\b2io.output\b4(\c9[\b7file\c9:\b3string\c9 or \b5FILE*\c9]\b4)\c9: \b5FILE*\c9
\t\tSimilar to \b2io.input\c9, but returns and modifies the current output stream.

\t\b2io.write\b4(\b7...\c9: \b3strings\c9 or \b5numbers\b4)\c9
\t\tEquivalent to \b2io.output\b4()\c9:\b2write\b4(\b7...\b4)\c9.

\t\b2io.read\b4(\b7...\b4)\c9: \b7...\c9
\t\tReads from the current input stream.  Equivalent to \b2io.input\b4()\c9:\b2read\b4(\b7...\b4)\c9.

\t\b2io.lines\b4(\c9[\b7file\c9:\b3string\c9]\b4)\c9: \b2function\c9
\t\tReturns an iterator which, when called, returns successive lines from either \b3file\c9 or the standard output.

